<!--
Perceive-act loop, v1. One process: the shared always-socket agent (`agent.bsx`) plus two
in-process mock clients, a mock head and a mock body, that connect back over the socket.
Run it; the agent socket server default-boots, so no --server flag is needed:

    beet --main=examples/perceive_act/main-v1.bsx

The agent's capability routes forward over the socket to whichever client serves them:
`take-photo`/`speak-text`/`set-emotion` to the head, `drive` to the body. The
head captures the floor-photo fixtures, speaks via `tts` and logs the emotion; the body
records the drive command. The loop runs until Ctrl+C.

Only the body client differs from v2 (which swaps the mock body for a wgpu fox), so the
agent block is factored into `agent.bsx` and shared verbatim.

Needs `OPENAI_API_KEY` (the agent) and the kokoro `tts` on PATH for spoken audio.
-->
<Fragment>
	<!-- the agent + fixtures live workspace-relative, so this entry roots there -->
	<StoreRoot src="../.."/>
	<CrateCheck features="thread,sockets"/>
	<Template src="examples/perceive_act/agent.bsx"/>
	<!-- in-process clients, each its own socket root -->
	<MockHead url="ws://127.0.0.1:8338"/>
	<MockBody url="ws://127.0.0.1:8338"/>
</Fragment>
